MISSING OBJECT DETECTION
Missing object detection allows you to designate

00:01:21.869 --> 00:01:23.719
a high value object to monitor.

00:01:23.719 --> 00:01:26.450
The moment it is removed
from its position, an alarm can be triggered

00:01:26.450 --> 00:01:27.600
or alerts sent.

00:01:27.600 --> 00:01:30.670
This feature is ideal for keeping an eye on
valuable equipment and items.

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:32.619
The camera is always watching so you don’t
have to be.

00:01:32.619 --> 00:01:34.871
UNATTENDED OBJECT DETECTION
Like missing object detection, unattended

00:01:34.871 --> 00:01:37.530
object detection allows you to designate a
zone in the camera’s

00:01:37.530 --> 00:01:40.119
view and detect when an object is left in
that area.

00:01:40.119 --> 00:01:42.509
For example, if a suspicious item appears,
the software

00:01:42.509 --> 00:01:45.950
will highlight that object on the screen and
can be configured to trigger an alarm or send

00:01:45.950 --> 00:01:46.950
an alert.

00:01:46.950 --> 00:01:50.549
This simple feature can help draw attention
to suspicious packages, potential threats,

00:01:50.549 --> 00:01:51.719
even lost items to be
returned to their owners.

00:01:51.719 --> 00:01:52.719
This feature is ideal for corridors, roads,
parking lots, breezeways, supply depots,

00:01:52.719 --> 00:01:53.719
perimeter fencing, mess halls, and many other
areas.

