FACIAL DETECTION
One of the key requirements of security systems

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:24.190
is monitoring who is entering and leaving
your facility and this feature

00:02:24.190 --> 00:02:26.420
is exceptionally useful to achieve that goal.

00:02:26.420 --> 00:02:29.440
The facial detection function in our NVR software
catalogs every face

00:02:29.440 --> 00:02:33.690
captured on video into a thumbnail index and
is time stamped for later use.

00:02:33.690 --> 00:02:36.700
This gives you a clear image of each person
that visits your location from the moment

00:02:36.700 --> 00:02:40.100
the face was detected to the moment that it
leaves the camera’s field of view.

00:02:40.100 --> 00:02:43.780
This level of documentation is unparalleled
and is highly recommended for use at all of

00:02:43.780 --> 00:02:45.730
your entrances and exits.

00:02:45.730 --> 00:02:46.980
OBJECT TRACKING
Object tracking is one of the many features

00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:47.980
that comes in our NVR software and can be
used on any camera in your

00:02:47.980 --> 00:02:48.980
surveillance system through the software interface.

00:02:48.980 --> 00:02:51.390
This view is from our 4 megapixel fisheye
camera and when you

00:02:51.390 --> 00:02:55.480
de-wrap the fisheye view into the 180° tri-view,
you have a much better view of the monitored

00:02:55.480 --> 00:02:56.480
area.

00:02:56.480 --> 00:02:59.250
The tracking feature automatically follows
movement in the camera’s field of view until

00:02:59.250 --> 00:03:02.140
